article_text:
Sioux Falls, SD

A dreary day did not stop a group of K-9s from enjoying the great outdoors.

The Annual Woofstock festival at Spencer Dog Park offers tail wagging fun for dogs of all sizes. Owners join their four legged friend for activities and a number of contests. For some the social atmosphere is what draws them to the event.

"He's about seven months old. We got him when he was a puppy, so he is skittish, and this is a great way to socialize him with people and other animals.” Jonna Sherlock said.

Awards were given out for a number of categories including cutest puppy and dog that looks most like their owner.
